news.title: In low-wage Portugal, Europe's housing crisis bites deep
news.para: The 57-year-old nursing home carer earns less than 800 euros ($845) a month, as do about a fourth of the country's workforce. For the last decade, she got by because she's been paying just 300 euros a month for her one-bedroom apartment in an undistinguished Lisbon neighborhood.

news.title: Maharashtra government revises guidelines for houses built, allotted by MHADA
news.para: As per the new guidelines, the apartments under MIG category will now be spread over up to 968 sq ft as against earlier permitted space of 1,722 sq ft. For HIG category, the carpet area has been increased from the limit of 2,152 sq ft to any configurations above 968 sq ft now.

news.title: Four years on, DDA finds two land parcels eligible to develop under land pooling policy
news.para: A DDA official confirmed receiving consensus on or expression of interest in pooling their holdings from landowners in Zone P-II, Sector 8B of the policy.

news.title: Two commercial buildings in Madurai with property tax arrears sealed
news.para: The first building is situated in ward 72 of zone V on Thiruparankundram Road and is owned by three people. The owners did not pay property tax since 2014-15 and the arrears amounted to 5.7 lakh for the last nine years.

news.title: Draft master plan for Delhi-2041 likely to be notified by March-end
news.para: ​The Delhi Development Authority (DDA) had earlier this month approved the draft master plan with Lt Governor VK Saxena highlighting its thrust for inclusive development, sustainability and innovative interventions such as transit-oriented development hubs, land pooling, heritage and Yamuna rejuvenation, and regeneration of the city.

news.title: Kolkata civic body set to offer paid tatkal service at doorstep, starting with property mutation
news.para: Services like issuance of birth certificates and copies of death certificates are to be brought under its ambit at a later stage. The proposal has been placed before the mayor, who is keen to implement it at the earliest, KMC sources said.

news.title: DDA offers buyback, reconstruction, flat swap options to owners of Signature View Apartments
news.para: ​Lieutenant Governor V K Saxena, who is also the chairman of the Delhi Development Authority, had ordered the body to redevelop the apartments in Delhi's Mukherjee Nagar and proactively support the thousands of residents facing "grave danger to life and property".

news.title: Kolkata civic body may set steep target for property tax department
news.para: Sources said the civic brass has asked to mop up at least 30% more revenue from property tax next fiscal. The KMC assessment department was asked to collect Rs 1,200 crore from property tax and mutation services. T

news.title: Goa: Building nod deemed if panchayat, BDO don't act within 60 days
news.para: The department has notified the amended Goa Panchayat Raj Act, passed by the state legislative assembly on January 18. Secretary for legal affairs Sandip Jacques issued the notification.

news.title: Bombay HC halts development of any kind in Bhagwati Greens Phase 2 till Mar 29
news.para: The HC bench of Justices Gautam Patel and Neela Gokhale on Wednesday was surprised at the March 6 MahaRERA order. The association of flat buyers had filed a complaint with MahaRERA, alleging the builder, Bhagwati Developers, had proposed a fourth tower in a "multi-play area".

news.title: Bombay HC advises tenants of 10-year stalled redevelopment project to choose new builder cautiously
news.para: A petition was filed by 44 tenants of Ratilal Mansion CHSL who have been in transit accommodation since 2009. The project was stalled in 2013 after the developer, Orbit Corporation, went into liquidation. At the site is a ground-plus-nine storey incomplete structure.

news.title: Gurugram: Three DTCP teams to check OCs by architects; report in three days
news.para: The teams will consist of assistant town planners and seven junior engineers, officials said on Thursday. They have to verify if the OCs are sound, and submit a report for at least 10% of all OCs granted within three days.

news.title: Piramal to sell DHFL loans to JM Financial ARC
news.para: Piramal Capital had initiated a Swiss Challenge against the ARC's anchor bid, inviting other interested bidders to submit expressions of interest by March 15, with the offer amount required to be a minimum of 10% higher than the base offer of ₹2,550 crore.

news.title: HDFC may contest IL&FS building sale to Brookfield
news.para: NCLAT had turned down HDFC's appeal for a stay on the sale of the property located in the Bandra Kurla Complex, which is regarded as one of the prime locations in Mumbai's business district.

news.title: Court asks CBI to file report in Orris India vs Godrej Properties case
news.para: OIPL has accused Godrej Properties of siphoning off funds from the project to other companies, a claim the latter denies and claims “an attempt to malign our image”.
